17:34.192 --> 17:36.527
to put that money back
into the account.

17:36.528 --> 17:38.796
- Spends her career
helping victims

17:38.797 --> 17:40.664
and then she steals
a settlement?

17:40.665 --> 17:42.266
- She found out
garvey was non compos

17:42.267 --> 17:44.301
and grabbed the opportunity.

17:44.302 --> 17:46.003
- Well, if she stole the money,

17:46.004 --> 17:47.704
she-she had to have a reason.

17:47.705 --> 17:49.039
- Greed?

17:49.040 --> 17:50.507
- Yeah, but she lives
within her means.

17:50.508 --> 17:52.342
I mean, she had three pairs
of shoes in her closet.

17:52.343 --> 17:54.278
- Maybe she was sick of it.

17:54.279 --> 17:55.979
- I.T. Retrieved and catalogued

17:55.980 --> 18:00.250
everything on Theresa's
home and office computers.

18:02.921 --> 18:04.888
This was erased from her iPad.

18:04.889 --> 18:07.424
We had to pull it
off the server.

18:07.425 --> 18:09.660
- "To whom it may concern.

18:09.661 --> 18:12.362
I took the money."

18:12.363 --> 18:15.232
Theresa's suicide note?

18:15.233 --> 18:18.068
- Looks like your
case just closed.

18:23.039 --> 18:24.006
We don't buy it.

18:24.007 --> 18:25.274
We need to go further

18:25.275 --> 18:26.742
before we can close
this as a suicide.

18:26.743 --> 18:28.844
- Why, because the
note's on an iPad?

18:28.845 --> 18:31.847
- Because of the embezzlement.

18:31.848 --> 18:33.815
- With that suicide note,

18:33.816 --> 18:37.553
no D.A.
In his right mind would file.

18:37.554 --> 18:41.590
Joe, don't be a moron.
We have legit suspects.

18:48.565 --> 18:50.999
- You give us the room a minute?

19:02.946 --> 19:05.180
Bobby, I appreciate
you coming back.

19:05.181 --> 19:07.583
I really do.

19:07.584 --> 19:12.487
But this doesn't work.

19:12.488 --> 19:14.256
I know what you do.

19:14.257 --> 19:17.259
And you know what I do.

19:17.260 --> 19:19.328
I've got your back,

19:19.329 --> 19:23.131
and you respect my face
and don't get in it.

19:29.305 --> 19:30.906
- Detective goren?

19:30.907 --> 19:32.674
I'm Paula geisen.

19:32.675 --> 19:34.676
Come on in.

19:34.677 --> 19:37.079
- Sorry I'm late.

19:37.080 --> 19:38.880
- Well, it's tough to
get away from your job.

19:38.881 --> 19:43.518
- No excuse.

19:43.519 --> 19:46.455
Your office, it's, uh, striking.

19:46.456 --> 19:47.556
- Thank you.

19:47.557 --> 19:49.925
- These two doors,

19:49.926 --> 19:52.761
they remind me of a riddle.

19:52.762 --> 19:54.329
You know the one?

19:54.330 --> 19:57.399
Two identical doors.

19:57.400 --> 19:59.868
Two identical guards.

19:59.869 --> 20:03.171
One guard is an angel
guarding heaven,

20:03.172 --> 20:05.140
he always tells the truth.

20:05.141 --> 20:08.277
And the other guard is
a devil guarding hell.

20:08.278 --> 20:10.045
He always has to lie.

20:10.046 --> 20:12.347
You have one question to ask

20:12.348 --> 20:15.951
to get into heaven.

20:15.952 --> 20:19.021
What would that question be?

20:19.022 --> 20:20.055
You'll never get it.

20:20.056 --> 20:23.325
It's...You'll...

20:23.326 --> 20:25.127
- Give me time.

20:25.128 --> 20:28.930
- Uh, also the
missed appointments,

20:28.931 --> 20:31.366
I apologize.

20:31.367 --> 20:35.237
- I'm sure you had good
reasons not to come.

20:35.238 --> 20:36.672
- You don't have to do that.

20:36.673 --> 20:39.741
- How do you mean?
- Empathize with me.

20:39.742 --> 20:42.210
- Is that what you
think I'm doing?

20:42.211 --> 20:44.513
- Yeah, "I'm sure you had
reason not to come."

20:44.514 --> 20:47.149
You know, "your job
is too tough...

20:47.150 --> 20:48.617
To get away from."

20:48.618 --> 20:52.020
You're trying to gain my trust.

20:52.021 --> 20:55.157
- I don't think that would
be that easy to do.

20:57.960 --> 21:00.195
- Is that what it
says in my file?

21:00.196 --> 21:01.797
- That?

21:01.798 --> 21:05.434
That's only part of your file.

21:05.435 --> 21:08.136
- Did you accept to do this

21:08.137 --> 21:10.605
before or after you read it?

21:10.606 --> 21:12.074
- After.

21:12.075 --> 21:14.109
- And after the more
experienced psychiatrists

21:14.110 --> 21:15.210
begged off?

21:15.211 --> 21:20.682
- I didn't have to
fight to get you.

21:20.683 --> 21:22.984
And it wasn't only the files.

21:25.588 --> 21:27.789
Seven employer-mandated sessions

21:27.790 --> 21:30.625
with someone...

21:30.626 --> 21:31.960
As challenging as you...

21:31.961 --> 21:36.531
- You were gonna say
"crazy," weren't you?

21:36.532 --> 21:38.734
- Why do you think that?

21:38.735 --> 21:42.671
- Do you think I'm crazy?

21:42.672 --> 21:44.840
- I think you are a person

21:44.841 --> 21:48.210
who is aware that the world
is a dangerous place.

21:48.211 --> 21:50.545
You found a way of surviving,

21:50.546 --> 21:54.449
but your way can
make other people

21:54.450 --> 21:56.752
feel uncomfortable.

21:59.422 --> 22:03.024
- "Challenging" and, you
know, "uncomfortable."

22:03.025 --> 22:05.827
You're walking on egg
shells with me, aren't you?

22:05.828 --> 22:08.497
- Isn't that how you like it?
Hmm?

22:08.498 --> 22:10.665
It's part of your skill set,

22:10.666 --> 22:13.301
like being able to
read people quickly.

22:16.672 --> 22:17.906
- It's my job.

22:17.907 --> 22:19.007
- Sure.

22:19.008 --> 22:20.876
It's protected you.

22:20.877 --> 22:23.412
But it's also taken its toll

22:23.413 --> 22:27.449
on those around you
and on yourself.

22:27.450 --> 22:30.152
You are exceptional
at analyzing others.

22:30.153 --> 22:34.022
Exceptional.

22:34.023 --> 22:36.825
So what is it that you
think will happen

22:36.826 --> 22:39.227
if you start looking
at yourself?

22:46.803 --> 22:48.403
- I didn't tell you
about the embezzlement

22:48.404 --> 22:49.971
because I didn't know.

22:49.972 --> 22:52.841
- So overseeing accounts isn't
part of the job description?

22:52.842 --> 22:54.843
- Oversee, not monitor
every transaction.

22:54.844 --> 22:57.813
- 2.7 million didn't
warrant your attention?

22:57.814 --> 22:59.214
- It's a great deal of money,

22:59.215 --> 23:00.682
but it's not an
atypical settlement.

23:00.683 --> 23:02.584
- Plus we thought we'd
settled with Alice garvey.

23:02.585 --> 23:04.052
We sent her the papers.

23:04.053 --> 23:09.090
- You said that you watched
mediation DVDs with Theresa.

23:09.091 --> 23:11.326
- Yeah, I did.

23:11.327 --> 23:13.328
- She was looking for
God's perfect match.

23:13.329 --> 23:15.096
Maybe you were it.

23:15.097 --> 23:17.032
- She was my boss.
We were just friends.

23:17.033 --> 23:19.334
- We are gonna let our lawyers
handle things from here on in.

23:19.335 --> 23:21.303
Obviously, we'll be doing
our own investigation.

23:21.304 --> 23:22.671
- So will we.

23:22.672 --> 23:24.506
There was a lamp on this table,

23:24.507 --> 23:26.308
and her pictures are gone.

23:26.309 --> 23:27.709
- Johnny let a friend of hers

23:27.710 --> 23:29.444
come in and take some of
her personal effects.

23:29.445 --> 23:31.546
- Is that Natalie?

23:31.547 --> 23:33.348
- Uh, yeah, they were buddies.

23:33.349 --> 23:34.950
- You let someone remove
possible evidence

23:34.951 --> 23:37.285
from an ongoing investigation?

23:37.286 --> 23:39.054
- We're bankers, not police.

23:42.124 --> 23:44.459
- Uh, I went to her office

23:44.460 --> 23:46.728
to box up her things
for her parents.

23:46.729 --> 23:48.296
I ran into Johnny.

23:48.297 --> 23:49.898
We talked a little.

23:49.899 --> 23:51.967
- Googled you.

23:51.968 --> 23:55.203
You were 57th in the
tennis rankings at 18.

23:55.204 --> 23:57.739
- Oh, ancient history.

23:57.740 --> 24:01.243
- Then drug possession and
petty theft in your 20s.

24:01.244 --> 24:04.312
And now you're over
$70,000 in debt.

24:04.313 --> 24:09.885
- 73,600, to be exact.

24:11.787 --> 24:12.921
- That's a cute cat.

24:12.922 --> 24:16.191
- Oh, um, name's pyewacket.

24:16.192 --> 24:18.660
- Pyewacket?

24:18.661 --> 24:19.728
That's from a...

24:19.729 --> 24:22.464
Jimmy Stewart film.

24:22.465 --> 24:28.603
Yeah, the cat, it was Kim
novak's best friend.

24:28.604 --> 24:30.839
It's a funny movie.

24:30.840 --> 24:32.641
I think the cat was a wizard.

24:32.642 --> 24:33.608
Not very catholic.

24:33.609 --> 24:36.278
- It's a cat.

24:36.279 --> 24:40.115
- So you and Theresa were
roommates at Georgetown.

24:40.116 --> 24:41.816
Very catholic.

24:41.817 --> 24:44.085
- She got me into rehab.

24:44.086 --> 24:46.421
Back into the church.

24:46.422 --> 24:48.924
- Did you know that-
that Theresa was accused

24:48.925 --> 24:50.792
of, uh, stealing
millions of dollars

24:50.793 --> 24:52.861
from the church
settlement account?

24:56.432 --> 24:58.600
Yeah, I know, it...

24:58.601 --> 25:00.135
Doesn't make sense.

25:00.136 --> 25:02.737
But there must have
been a reason.

25:02.738 --> 25:05.874
She didn't have a lot of
experience with men, did she?

25:05.875 --> 25:08.009
- How many straight,
single men in their 30s

25:08.010 --> 25:10.645
are still practicing catholics
and not total weirdoes?

25:10.646 --> 25:14.616
- Johnny's pretty cute.
How about him?

25:14.617 --> 25:17.185
- She was his boss. No way.

25:22.358 --> 25:27.195
- You're lying.

25:27.196 --> 25:28.763
- Okay.

25:28.764 --> 25:31.166
I mean, maybe they
hooked up once or tw&e,

25:31.167 --> 25:32.701
but it-it was casual.

25:32.702 --> 25:34.202
- They were friends, though.

25:34.203 --> 25:37.105
I mean, she liked him, though.

25:37.106 --> 25:39.341
- Yeah.

25:39.342 --> 25:41.576
A lot.

25:48.584 --> 25:50.952
- You lied to us, Johnny.

25:54.323 --> 25:58.893
- Johnny.
You slept with your boss.

25:58.894 --> 26:02.030
- All right, I'll
be honest with you,

26:02.031 --> 26:06.167
I didn't want to admit it
in front of kilpatrick.

26:06.168 --> 26:07.769
- Can't be that dumb.

26:07.770 --> 26:11.139
I mean, lying to two cops in
a homicide investigation?

26:11.140 --> 26:14.342
Really?
Did you just cop to a felony?

26:14.343 --> 26:17.145
- We hooked up a month ago.

26:17.146 --> 26:18.146
It was no big deal.

26:18.147 --> 26:19.781
Once, maybe twice.

26:19.782 --> 26:22.550
- So the pillow talk wasn't
about where to stash the 2.7?

26:22.551 --> 26:24.819
- This sounds like
I need a lawyer.

26:24.820 --> 26:26.988
- Do you need a lawyer?
I don't know.

26:26.989 --> 26:28.156
Right now you're just a...

26:28.157 --> 26:29.691
you're a person of interest.

26:29.692 --> 26:33.595
Lawyer up, well, that takes you
straight up to maybe suspect.

26:33.596 --> 26:36.097
- You guys, I didn't
steal the money.

26:37.099 --> 26:38.566
The night Theresa died,

26:38.567 --> 26:40.368
she called me and told
me that monsignor mcteal

26:40.369 --> 26:42.504
accused her of embezzlement.

26:42.505 --> 26:45.040
The next day Natalie told me

26:45.041 --> 26:47.142
he asked Theresa for sex

26:47.143 --> 26:50.912
in exchange for giving her five
days to replace the money.

26:50.913 --> 26:52.180
- What was your reaction?

26:52.181 --> 26:54.416
- I wanted to kill the bastard.

26:54.417 --> 26:58.553
I figured it had to be
an accounting mistake.

26:58.554 --> 27:00.021
- No, no, no. She stole it.

27:00.022 --> 27:01.256
There's no question about that.

27:01.257 --> 27:04.959
- No. You're wrong.

27:04.960 --> 27:06.528
We both felt the same way.

27:06.529 --> 27:08.830
The only people that
deserved that money

27:08.831 --> 27:11.399
are victims.

27:13.135 --> 27:16.871
- So the monsignor forced
Theresa to have sex

27:16.872 --> 27:18.807
quid pro quo

27:18.808 --> 27:21.476
for giving her five days
to return the money?

27:21.477 --> 27:24.112
- She's so remorseful,
she kills herself.

27:26.749 --> 27:28.983
- Five days to return the money,

27:28.984 --> 27:33.822
she goes home and kills herself.

27:33.823 --> 27:35.824
You know, look at this.

27:35.825 --> 27:39.027
Uh...

27:39.028 --> 27:40.929
"What I have now done

27:40.930 --> 27:42.831
was the only path left for me."

27:42.832 --> 27:45.233
- So formal.
- Yeah.

27:45.234 --> 27:46.935
- Here all night?

27:46.936 --> 27:49.003
- You bring bagels?

27:49.004 --> 27:52.407
- See, men, women, they
leave different markers

27:52.408 --> 27:54.375
when they write suicide notes.

27:54.376 --> 27:57.212
Women seem to rely more heavily

27:57.213 --> 27:59.380
on expression of feelings,

27:59.381 --> 28:02.217
like, um, thanking someone.

28:02.218 --> 28:04.519
You know, polite speech.
Apologizing.

28:04.520 --> 28:05.887
- She was close to her parents,

28:05.888 --> 28:07.722
and they're not even mentioned.

28:07.723 --> 28:09.090
- Yes.

28:13.295 --> 28:16.898
"I acted out of greed
and poor character."

28:16.899 --> 28:18.566
See, now that's a
direct admission,

28:18.567 --> 28:22.237
but there's no reference
to God or the Bible,

28:22.238 --> 28:25.540
or any misgivings for breaking
the eighth commandment.

28:25.541 --> 28:29.477
- The $2.7 million question is...

28:29.478 --> 28:31.780
Why was it erased?

28:31.781 --> 28:34.015
- Yeah, I don't know.

28:34.016 --> 28:38.987
But I do know that
she didn't write it.

28:38.988 --> 28:43.358
The killer wants her death
to look like a suicide,

28:43.359 --> 28:47.362
but he puts the gun four
feet away from the body.

28:47.363 --> 28:49.898
Doesn't make any sense.

28:49.899 --> 28:51.599
- The cat.

28:51.600 --> 28:53.768
- Yes, I have pyewacket.

28:53.769 --> 28:55.870
I decided to keep him.

28:55.871 --> 28:58.406
- You ever feed him when
Theresa worked late,

28:58.407 --> 29:00.441
or when she was out of town?

29:00.442 --> 29:02.710
- Um, can I get
back to my lesson?

29:02.711 --> 29:04.779
- So you have your own
key to her apartment?

29:04.780 --> 29:06.414
- No.

29:06.415 --> 29:08.416
- Is that why you asked the
building super to let you in?

29:08.417 --> 29:10.151
- Right.

29:10.152 --> 29:12.554
- You wanted him
to corroborate you

29:12.555 --> 29:14.422
finding the dead body.

29:14.423 --> 29:16.925
But you already
knew she was dead.

29:16.926 --> 29:21.095
- I don't have a key.

29:21.096 --> 29:22.697
- Well, we got a warrant.

29:22.698 --> 29:24.933
We searched your apartment.

29:29.371 --> 29:32.473
- Fine. I had a key.

29:32.474 --> 29:36.077
- Neighbor says she saw you
heading up the stairs at 8:15.

29:36.078 --> 29:39.480
Constantine says you
got him at 8:35.

29:39.481 --> 29:41.249
Maybe you found a way

29:41.250 --> 29:43.585
to access Theresa's
account at work.

29:43.586 --> 29:46.754
When Theresa tipped onto
it, you killed her.

29:46.755 --> 29:50.892
- That's ridiculous.
She was my best friend.

29:50.893 --> 29:56.731
- Uh, now she turned
your life around.

29:56.732 --> 29:58.933
Didn't she?

29:58.934 --> 30:03.905
And you'd do anything
to protect her.

30:03.906 --> 30:05.673
And in the eyes of
the catholic church,

30:05.674 --> 30:08.409
a suicide is the same as murder.

30:14.316 --> 30:17.585
- When Tess didn't answer,

30:17.586 --> 30:21.089
I let myself in.

30:21.090 --> 30:23.524
I found her on the
floor of the bedroom,

30:23.525 --> 30:25.627
and she'd shot herself.

30:28.497 --> 30:30.732
She wouldn't be
able to have a mass

30:30.733 --> 30:33.835
or be buried in
consecrated ground.

30:33.836 --> 30:36.871
- So you kicked the gun away
and you repositioned the body.

30:36.872 --> 30:41.542
- She committed suicide, but
the monsignor was responsible.

30:41.543 --> 30:45.013
- That's why you erased the
suicide note on her iPad.

30:49.118 --> 30:51.886
- What suicide note?

31:01.528 --> 31:03.695
Natalie admits she
dutched the crime scene.

31:03.696 --> 31:04.596
That's obstruction.

31:04.631 --> 31:06.832
- So who erased
the suicide note?

31:06.833 --> 31:10.169
- Not Natalie. The killer?

31:10.170 --> 31:11.637
- Why?

31:11.638 --> 31:14.139
- As a fail-safe.

31:14.140 --> 31:16.075
Police close the
case as a suicide,

31:16.076 --> 31:17.610
then he's home free.

31:17.611 --> 31:19.879
If not, then he knows that
they'll scrub her computers

31:19.880 --> 31:21.280
and find the note.

31:21.281 --> 31:25.184
- Natalie said Hugh
mcteal extorted Theresa.

31:25.185 --> 31:27.386
- She didn't realllly
say that, captain.

31:27.387 --> 31:28.721
- Maybe not word for word,

31:28.722 --> 31:32.324
but close enough.

31:32.325 --> 31:35.060
Let's bring him in and sweat
him for suspicion of rape.

31:37.197 --> 31:41.901
- Did you rape Theresa esperna?

31:41.902 --> 31:43.002
- Absolutely not.

31:43.003 --> 31:44.670
Is that why you
brought me in here?

31:44.671 --> 31:45.971
- Look, if your strategy

31:45.972 --> 31:47.306
is to drag the church
through the mud...

31:47.307 --> 31:49.875
- we have no agenda
against the church.

31:49.876 --> 31:52.077
For every story you
hear of misconduct,

31:52.078 --> 31:55.548
there are thousands of
stories of good works.

31:55.549 --> 31:57.383
- Well, that's the first

31:57.384 --> 32:00.586
true thing you've said
all day, detective.

32:00.587 --> 32:02.755
- You know, I was thinking,

32:02.756 --> 32:06.292
you know, an episcopalian
priest can...

32:06.293 --> 32:07.359
well, they can have a wife,

32:07.360 --> 32:09.595
and a lutheran pastor,

32:09.596 --> 32:11.297
they can date a playmate.

32:11.298 --> 32:14.199
You have, uh, vows of chastity.

32:14.200 --> 32:16.001
- Mm.

32:16.002 --> 32:18.871
A vocation demands sacrifice.

32:18.872 --> 32:22.575
- Jeez, it must be...
Frustrating.

32:24.177 --> 32:26.312
- Temptation is a test

32:26.313 --> 32:27.546
that God gives all of us.

32:27.547 --> 32:29.214
- Well, it seems to be
a test you're failing.

32:29.215 --> 32:30.716
- I'm no different
from any other man.

32:30.717 --> 32:32.651
How about you, detective goren?

32:32.652 --> 32:34.587
Any frailties of your own?

32:34.588 --> 32:36.188
- Look, we're within
a minute of walking

32:36.189 --> 32:40.526
if we don't hear a charge.

32:40.527 --> 32:41.961
- You can...

32:41.962 --> 32:45.998
Love the church for
their good works,

32:45.999 --> 32:47.533
or you can hate the church

32:47.534 --> 32:51.337
for their...Hypocrisy.

32:51.338 --> 32:55.741
Tick tock.
Ti- how much time do I have left?

32:55.742 --> 32:58.277
Go ahead. No. How much?

33:03.750 --> 33:07.286
But both sides agree...

33:09.522 --> 33:12.658
Thou shalt not kill.

33:12.659 --> 33:16.261
- I did not kill Theresa.

33:16.262 --> 33:18.163
- Okay, forget about the murder.

33:18.164 --> 33:21.967
Theresa's friend says you
forced her to have sex.

33:21.968 --> 33:23.302
- Never happened.

33:23.303 --> 33:26.438
- Well, there's no way we
can prove it forensically,

33:26.439 --> 33:30.442
because you're careful,
and used a condom.

33:30.443 --> 33:31.877
Oh, I forgot.

33:31.878 --> 33:34.880
That's another sin, isn't it?

33:34.881 --> 33:37.583
You're...

33:37.584 --> 33:39.118
The consoler?

33:39.119 --> 33:40.486
- Don't push it, detective.

33:40.487 --> 33:42.821
- You take advantage
of vulnerable women.

33:42.822 --> 33:45.658
